### Issue details

Not sure if this is a bug or intended given the flags, so filing as a question.

With `--rename-flags none`, a nested class whose simple name equals an enclosing class's simple name is emitted unchanged, which does not compile (JLS 8.1: a member class may not have the same simple name as any enclosing class).

`RenameVisitor.checkNames` returns early when the rename flags are empty ([RenameVisitor.java#L50](https://github.com/skylot/jadx/blob/8c28a8530e0fb2d2caba930b38f0f936f118d490/jadx-core/src/main/java/jadx/core/dex/visitors/rename/RenameVisitor.java#L50)), so no name checks run; the inner-vs-enclosing collision check also sits behind `args.isRenameValid()` ([RenameVisitor.java#L120](https://github.com/skylot/jadx/blob/8c28a8530e0fb2d2caba930b38f0f936f118d490/jadx-core/src/main/java/jadx/core/dex/visitors/rename/RenameVisitor.java#L120)). With any renaming enabled jadx already handles it (renames the inner, reason `collision with other inner class name`), so this only shows with renaming fully off. If `none` is meant to leave every name untouched even when the output is not valid Java, this is working as intended.

### Sample

`Outer.smali` (class `a`, obfuscated so its member class is also named `a`):

```smali
.class public La;
.super Ljava/lang/Object;

.annotation system Ldalvik/annotation/MemberClasses;
    value = {
        La$a;
    }
.end annotation
```

`Inner.smali`:

```smali
.class public La$a;
.super Ljava/lang/Object;

.annotation system Ldalvik/annotation/EnclosingClass;
    value = La;
.end annotation

.annotation system Ldalvik/annotation/InnerClass;
    accessFlags = 0x9
    name = "a"
.end annotation
```

`jadx --rename-flags none` output (does not compile):

```java
public class a {
    public static class a {
    }
}
```

Default flags decompile the same input correctly:

```java
public class a {
    /* JADX INFO: renamed from: a$a, reason: collision with other inner class name */
    public static class C0000a {
    }
}
```

